President Joe Biden and Prime Minister Boris Johnson recently had a conversation regarding the situation in Afghanistan. They praised the courage and expertise of their military and civilian personnel who are jointly involved in the evacuation efforts in Kabul, aimed at rescuing their citizens and Afghan nationals who aided in the war. The leaders also emphasized the importance of ongoing collaboration and coordination among allies and democratic partners on Afghanistan policy. They discussed potential avenues for the global community to offer additional humanitarian aid and support to refugees and vulnerable Afghans. Furthermore, they agreed to convene a virtual G7 leaders' meeting in the coming week to establish a unified strategy and approach.